<subSubSection id="A7471054E37EA0FACE8A1D8993CFDFB3" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" type="description">
<paragraph id="1771307C045988CC0BFB97CCDC4B0063" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BC8254503397E5CA9622FDD7F72B52E0" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">
Herbs perennial, 15-40 cm tall, hispid, strigose. Stems single or several (1-4) arise from rosettes, caspitose, erect, not branched, usually pale straw to light brown, densely covered with long white spreading bristles. Basal leaves short petiolate, linear to linear-oblanceolate, 10-23 cm 
<normalizedToken id="1C9541048E2807DAB641C1A253CE4D7B" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3-10 mm, abaxially densely pubescent and hispid along rised midrib and margin, reticulate venation, adaxially densely appressed hispid and short strigose, base attenuate, apex acute; Cauline leaves sessile, lanceolate, 2-5 cm 
<normalizedToken id="A4FFFE0EFCC7361F8248B7C14E1D896B" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.5-5 mm. Inflorescences terminal, solitary or dichotomously branched, 4-8 cm wide at anthesis, length to 11 cm in fruit, flowers 5-20; bracts lanceolate to linear-oblanceolate, 1.2-2 cm 
<normalizedToken id="C5CE8F0D52CDCE60A3E477EBDA1EFA96" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.2-4.5 mm, densely hispid, short strigose. Pedicel short, ca. 5 mm. Calyx 1.5-2.3 cm 
<normalizedToken id="459171BA206C8F2B4FDD89819D8C04EC" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1-2 mm, densely hispid, short strigose, parted nearly to base; lobes linear. Corolla cream above middle, light yellow below middle, clavate, 2.2-2.7 cm, base ca. 2 mm wide, gradually expanded upward; throat ca. 5 mm wide, obscurely pubescent outside, glabrous inside; lobes broadly triangular, ca. 1.5 
<normalizedToken id="CA72FB8EAD1F1D3221283D6AAF410852" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3 mm. Filaments subulate, 9-11 mm, decurrent; anthers united only at base, 7-8 mm, included, apex sterile, ca. 2 mm. Style 2.4-2.8 cm, glabrous. Nectary ca. 1 mm, glabrous. Pollen grains isopolar, tricolporate and prolate, polar axis (P) 21.91 
<normalizedToken id="5CB655A24FB240EBDB19923BE06FED57" originalValue="±">+/-</normalizedToken>
1.19 
<normalizedToken id="13D6F37D7FF4C25F0E5A6C7D0BFAFBF6" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, equatorial axis (E) 13.83 
<normalizedToken id="946C00AB6D4D86F43F783B0370C9E93B" originalValue="±">+/-</normalizedToken>
0.17 
<normalizedToken id="E0451B4652B799127D175D9E1D3710DD" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, P/E ratio 1.58. Nutlets gray-brown, ca. 5 mm 
<normalizedToken id="FD6193CF95D50DE54B096AA45AE8A01C" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3 mm, lustrous, smooth, ventral keeled, stipitate cicatrix.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B5A69F869B16E7367EAB4A8EE87B0A82" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" type="phenology">
<paragraph id="C91E0230055F013703F74BE32DC2A9CC" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">Phenology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6E986BAE7DC83CDB29B95E3F3D37F6C8" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">Flowering and fruiting occurs from May to July.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B86B51764229AA7168DE702ABD466ACA" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8665B02269E38862A20F38C719AF60E0" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="58035765A31F0506DD5E99D3ACDC9E92" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">The specific epithet of the new species refers to its type locality, Fuyun County, Xinjiang, China.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="276003BCCC911E1D68DDBC3D2D4CF2B3" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="F11C8312FF3604E2972C948170318E64" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">Distribution and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F104E3A4D0C299EAB6512264DB8C6C8E" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">
<taxonomicName id="65D443CF676143919E85F8548743440E" authorityName="Y. He &amp; Q. R. Liu" authorityYear="2020" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Onosma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Onosma fuyunensis" order="Boraginales" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fuyunensis">
<emphasis id="265776D434B50847D658EDBE13709471" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">Onosma fuyunensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is mainly distributed in Fuyun County, Qinghe County and Altay Prefecture (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="28B72E972BA844A3B5E991D81A3F0B07" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Distribution map of O. fuyunensis. Red points denote localities. Illustrated by Feng Xue and Yi He." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.144.33287.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/389937" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">4</figureCitation>
), it is also known from W Mongolia near the border (Khovd aimag), according to the photo record by Peter Kosachev (http://www.plantarium.ru/page/image/id/128255.html). It prefers dry rocky screes and upland meadows along the hillside, from 500-1400 m a.s.l. Species growing nearby are: 
<taxonomicName id="A8AD4BFB49E9201D10CB0160ABA38C0D" class="Mammalia" family="Tenrecidae" genus="Echinops" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Echinops gmelinii" order="Afrosoricida" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gmelinii">
<emphasis id="DE4D5B259D079F1717F8574D7DBD4DD1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">Echinops gmelinii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Turcz, 
<taxonomicName id="08A5941CF0713BA37BC9C37EAEED0017" authorityName="Boiss" authorityYear="1848" baseAuthorityName="L." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plumbaginaceae" genus="Goniolimon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Goniolimon speciosum" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="speciosum">
<emphasis id="EFE1D8328DEDD25EB1AEE76E7263781A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">Goniolimon speciosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(L.) Boiss., 
<taxonomicName id="3BC95CC56A9464DA3B5D14BC61FB9335" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Artemisia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Artemisia rutifolia subsp. var. var. altaica" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="rutifolia" subSpecies="var." variety="altaica">Artemisia rutifolia var. altaica</taxonomicName>
(Kryl.) Krasch. and 
<taxonomicName id="DC9DC9428FB1CFC11A531CDD885CB447" class="Liliopsida" family="Cyperaceae" genus="Carex" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Carex turkestanica" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="turkestanica">
<emphasis id="A1A4DF5C2EA57D932DF1CD6833B6C3BC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">Carex turkestanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Regel.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DBBA8269A802BE2D5B2E9F635AD905FB" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.144.33287.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/389937" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" start="Figure 4" startId="F4">
<paragraph id="63EBD52C744BA2BCAB4D029C9B976608" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">
